		<div class="entry-content"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/02/19/today-in-small-business-the-minimum-wage-debate-continues/" data-title="Today in Small Business: The Minimum Wage Debate Continues" data-description="The best business credit cards. How Converse uses social media. Why one owner in Illinois is closing her business.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ <a href="//www.nytimes.com/reuters/2014/02/18/business/18reuters-usa-fed-consumerdebt.html?">Consumer debt rose</a> in the fourth quarter by the most since 2007, and here&#8217;s <a href="//finance.fortune.cnn.com/2014/02/18/us-consumer-debt/">whatâs good, bad and ugly</a> about the trend.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Home builder sentiment <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/economy-policy/2014/02/18/homebuilder-sentiment-plunges-in-december/">plunged</a> in February.</p>
